properties.headline: High Surf Advisory issued January 23 at 2:58PM HST until January 24 at 6:00AM HST by NWS Honolulu HI
properties.description:
...HIGH SURF ADVISORY FOR NORTH AND WEST FACING SHORES OF NIIHAU
KAUAI OAHU MOLOKAI AND NORTH FACING SHORES OF MAUI AND WEST FACING
SHORES OF THE BIG ISLAND...

.The current northwest swell will steadily decline tonight and
will drop to borderline advisory thresholds by Friday. Another
large northwest swell will fill in Friday night and will likely
bring warning level surf on Saturday.

* WHAT...Surf of 16 to 24 feet along north and west facing shores
Niihau and Kauai, and north facing shores of Oahu, Molokai and
Maui. Surf of 12 to 18 feet along west facing shores of Oahu and
Molokai. Surf of 6 to 9 feet along west facing shores of the
Big Island..

* WHERE...Portions of Kauai, Maui, Molokai, Niihau, Oahu and the
Big Island Hawaii.

* WHEN...Until 6 AM HST Friday.

* IMPACTS...Moderate. Expect strong breaking waves, shore break,
and strong longshore and rip currents making swimming
difficult and dangerous.
properties.instruction:
Beachgoers, swimmers, and surfers should heed all advice given by
ocean safety officials and exercise caution.
